# Kurmi, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Kurmi () is a rural locality (a selo) in Gergebilsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 1,510 as of 2010. There are 14 streets.
Geography
Kurmi is located 5&nbsp;km southwest of Gergebil (the district's administrative centre) by road, on the right bank of the Karakoysu River. Khvartikuni and Murada are the nearest rural localities.
